3
00:00:11,679 --> 00:00:14,719
We will see during this module
essentially the three states of

4
00:00:14,719 --> 00:00:17,789
matter: gas, solid, and liquid.

5
00:00:17,789 --> 00:00:22,039
For a simple body, it is common to
consider three states of matter.

6
00:00:22,039 --> 00:00:25,400
The first state of matter
is the solid state,

7
00:00:25,480 --> 00:00:28,300
which corresponds to a material at 
low temperature

8
00:00:28,390 --> 00:00:31,589
at the molecular scale, there will be
a regular

9
00:00:31,589 --> 00:00:36,559
arrangement of atoms or molecules.
The liquid state will correspond

10
00:00:36,559 --> 00:00:40,160
to a material at low temperature and 
at high pressure.

11
00:00:40,160 --> 00:00:43,580
We will begin to have 
a local disorder,

12
00:00:43,580 --> 00:00:46,400
an agitation of the molecules 
or atoms.

13
00:00:46,420 --> 00:00:49,070
The gaseous state, the third state,

14
00:00:49,070 --> 00:00:52,180
corresponds to a material at
high temperature and

15
00:00:52,180 --> 00:00:53,420
at low pressure.

16
00:00:53,420 --> 00:00:55,880
At the molecular scale, 
we will notice

17
00:00:55,880 --> 00:00:58,600
a large agitation of the molecules 
or the atoms.

18
